Prompt:

Create a Python console program for a COM 103 project task tracker.

The program must:

* Ask for a project title and group name, and repeatedly prompt the user if either input is empty (no blank or whitespace-only input allowed).
* Display a fixed list of 5 predefined task types with corresponding hours:
  Program Logic / Coding (6h)
  UI / Output Formatting (3h)
  Testing & Debugging (2h)
  Documentation / README (2h)
  Presentation Slides (2h)
* Allow the user to assign up to 4 tasks, one at a time:

  * User selects a task number (1–5) or enters 0 to skip.
  * Validate that the input is numeric and within range.
  * Ask for member name (must not be empty).
  * Ask for status (“done” or “pending”) and validate input.
* Assign points:

  * 2 points if done
  * 1 point if pending
* Store all task details using lists (names, status, task type, hours, and points).
* Compute total points earned, maximum possible points, and progress percentage.
* Determine project status:

  * 75% and above → “PROJECT READY!”
  * 50%–74% → “ON TRACK.”
  * Below 50% → “NEEDS MORE WORK!”
* Display a formatted task board showing:

  * Project title and group name
  * Each assigned task with member, status, hours, and points
  * Final totals, progress percentage, and project status
* Use while loops, input validation, and basic Python only (no advanced libraries).
* Keep the output clean, aligned, and readable using formatted strings.

